{{Distinguish|Globe Theatre, Boston (1871)}}
[[Image:2010 EmpireGarden 690 WashingtonSt Boston USA 5087919947.jpg|thumb|right|The Globe Theatre building, Boston, in 2010]] The '''Globe Theatre''' (est. 1903) was a [[Theater (structure)|playhouse]] and cinema in [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]], located on [[Washington Street (Boston)|Washington Street]] in [[Chinatown, Boston|Chinatown]]. Architect [[Arthur H. Vinal]] designed the building in 1903;<ref>{{cite journal |title=New Globe Theatre, Boston, Mass. Arthur H. Vinal, Architect |journal=The Brickbuilder |volume=XII |issue= 9 |date=September 1903 }}</ref> it stands today at no.692 Washington St. opposite LaGrange Street, near the corner of Beach Street. In the 1910s it was also known as "Loew's Globe Theatre."<ref>"Loew's Globe Theatre." Boston register and business directory. 1918</ref>
==Performances/Screenings== {{col-begin}} {{col-1-of-2}}
